news.title: Two stalled housing projects in Noida back on track
news.para: The NCR-based property developers have started development work on over 1.5 million sq ft of space after clearing the dues of the lenders and the state urban development authority.

news.title: Gurugram: Illegal buildings & walls built on 18 acres razed in DTCP drive
news.para: Developers had allegedly started unauthorised plotting and construction in violation of urban planning regulations in three villages, Karanki, Sancholi and Daulha.

news.title: ED searches at 13 locations in Vasai-Virar over illegal buildings case
news.para: The developers constructed these buildings using falsified documents, fabricated approvals and fraudulent sale agreements, the ED said.

news.title: Odisha government plans to overhaul resettlement & rehabilitation policy
news.para: After the meeting, revenue minister Suresh Pujari said many private industries acquired more plots than needed and could not utilise them properly, even after 10-15 years.

news.title: Hyderabad development body pushes land pooling schemes to boost revenue
news.para: According to HMDA sources, land pooling initiatives covering approximately 300 acres are currently being developed in Pratap Singaram, Lemur, and Inmulnarva (near Kothur).

news.title: Government appoints Odisha RERA chairperson, two other members
news.para: Asit Kumar Mohapatra was appointed as ORERA chairman, while Rajendra Mishra and Shyam Sundar Dash will join as the other two members.

news.title: Delhi civic body identifies commercial users paying residential tax
news.para: Aiming to increase its tax collection for the financial year 2025-26 and identify defaulters, the civic body is referencing the electricity bills generated by the power discoms.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh government to cap registration fee for rent agreements
news.para: The department of stamp and registration is working on a proposal to reduce and cap the registration amount for lease deeds. The changes are being considered in light of the existing rules, under which registration is an expensive exercise.

news.title: Haryana government backs HC order to act against unauthorised construction in DLF areas
news.para: ​SC is likely to deliver a ruling next week in the case. The verdict is likely to have far-reaching consequences for thousands of residents and commercial establishments in one of the city's most prominent residential areas.

news.title: Telengana RERA penalises builder for nine-year delay in handing over villa to owners
news.para: The complainants – Neelima Vanamala and Srikanth Leburu, residents of Tellapur – had booked Villa No. 113 in Oct 2014 for a total cost of 73.4 lakh.

news.title: Noida: Recovery notices ignored, offices of 12 builders sealed over ₹175 crore dues
news.para: Antariksh Engineers, Elegant Infracon, Ansal Hitech, Rudra Buildwell and Uttam Steels, among others, were issued multiple recovery notices but had not responded, officials said.

news.title: Register plot or refund buyer for project delay: Telangana RERA to builder
news.para: The complainant, Purshottam Ketepally of Tarnaka, alleged he had paid 1.08 lakh to book a plot in the project in Oct 2022 and later signed a sale agreement on Dec 7, 2022, after paying an additional 4.09 lakh.

news.title: Free sand royalty receipts to be delivered to beneficiaries of housing schemes: Maharashtra revenue minister
news.para: The state government has adopted a policy to provide free sand for these houses. However, complaints have been received that the sand is not reaching the beneficiaries, Chandrashekhar Bawankule said.

news.title: Aditya Birla Real Estate posts net loss of ₹127 crore in Q4 FY25
news.para: For 2024-25, the company posted a net loss of Rs 148.74 crore as against a net profit of Rs 128.25 crore in the preceding year. Total income rose to Rs 1,257.33 crore from Rs 1,148.71 crore.

news.title: Akzo Nobel India's profit marginally down at ₹108.4 crore in Q4 FY25
news.para: Consolidated revenue from operations in the March quarter stood at Rs 1,022.1 crore as against Rs 973.4 crore in the year-ago period, said the maker of Dulux Paints.

news.title: Thiruvananthapuram: Technopark invites ₹381 crore tender for IT building under 'QUAD' project
news.para: The tender is being floated under a two-bid system consisting of prequalification and techno-commercial bid and the estimated project cost is Rs 380.08 crore, it said.

news.title: Germany's PBB not to take on new business in USA, citing volatility
news.para: The lender, also known as PBB, said it would evaluate "all options" for its existing U.S. business, without elaborating. The U.S. is PBB's second biggest market, making up 14% of its loan portfolio.

news.title: Shree Cement's profit declines 16% to ₹556 crore in Q4 FY25
news.para: ​Revenue from operations was higher at Rs 5,240 crore in Q4 FY25, up from Rs 5073 crore in the year-ago quarter, while the EBITDA remained steady at Rs 1,381 crore, the company said in a statement.

news.title: Fitch downgrades China Vanke further on liquidity concerns
news.para: Fitch downgraded long-term foreign- and local-currency issuer default ratings (IDRs) for the embattled property developer to 'CCC+' from 'B-'.

news.title: Berger Paints India's net profit up 18% at ₹262.91 crore in Q4 FY25
news.para: Consolidated revenue from operations in the quarter under review stood at Rs 2,704.03 crore against Rs 2,520.28 crore in the year-ago period, it added.
